1
00:00:49,133 --> 00:00:53,667
[Sung Jae's Dining Table]

2
00:00:55,367 --> 00:00:57,633
Dad, I'm home!

3
00:00:57,633 --> 00:01:00,000
Oh, Sung Jae, you're here.

4
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:01,633
Yeah.

5
00:01:04,200 --> 00:01:06,067
What is that smell?

6
00:01:09,200 --> 00:01:10,833
Whoa!

7
00:01:10,833 --> 00:01:13,200
Are you making seaweed soup for my birthday?

8
00:01:13,200 --> 00:01:14,600
It's not yours. Don't get any ideas.

9
00:01:14,600 --> 00:01:16,933
Huh? What? Then whose is it?

10
00:01:16,933 --> 00:01:20,533
Who do you think? The one who went
through a lot to give birth to you.

11
00:01:20,533 --> 00:01:22,300
Sung Jae, look.

12
00:01:22,300 --> 00:01:23,933
Doesn't it look good?

13
00:01:24,667 --> 00:01:27,900
Dad, you still like Mom that much?

14
00:01:27,900 --> 00:01:30,767
Do you know what I think about when I cook?

15
00:01:30,767 --> 00:01:33,667
"I should make this really well
and bring it to Su Yeon."

16
00:01:33,667 --> 00:01:35,000
That's what I always think.

17
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:37,467
I'm feeling kind of hurt.

18
00:01:37,467 --> 00:01:39,133
I'll just have to buy seaweed soup myself.

19
00:01:39,133 --> 00:01:41,167
Well? Should I walk you through the recipe?

20
00:01:41,167 --> 00:01:44,433
Nah, I'm not much of a cook.

21
00:01:44,433 --> 00:01:46,867
I've got no talent or interest in it.

22
00:01:46,867 --> 00:01:51,767
You'll need to cook sea urchin roe
seaweed soup for your girlfriend to love you.

23
00:01:51,767 --> 00:01:55,712
Do you know the secret weapon
for sea urchin roe seaweed soup?

24
00:01:57,367 --> 00:01:59,900
Isn't it just about fresh sea urchin?

25
00:01:59,900 --> 00:02:02,033
No, no.

26
00:02:02,833 --> 00:02:05,133
This! This!

27
00:02:05,133 --> 00:02:09,567
If you just add this to the sea urchin roe
seaweed soup, it'll become

28
00:02:09,567 --> 00:02:14,633
insanely good, just insanely good.

29
00:02:16,567 --> 00:02:18,533
Battalion commander!

30
00:02:21,500 --> 00:02:25,167
- Battalion Commander!
- Battalion Commander!

31
00:02:30,533 --> 00:02:33,967
[Episode 2]

32
00:02:33,967 --> 00:02:35,667
Sir, you can't leave us like this!

33
00:02:35,667 --> 00:02:37,100
The country still needs you!

34
00:02:37,100 --> 00:02:40,133
You lunatics, what on earth
did you do to the seaweed soup?

35
00:02:40,133 --> 00:02:42,367
Get him to the medical unit now!

36
00:02:42,367 --> 00:02:44,000
Quiet!

37
00:02:45,900 --> 00:02:47,600
Civil...

38
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:50,033
Civil...

39
00:02:50,033 --> 00:02:52,500
I'll make sure to tell
your wife you love her!

40
00:02:55,167 --> 00:02:57,967
Civilian hospital...

41
00:02:57,967 --> 00:03:00,600
Not the medical unit.
Get him to the nearest civilian hospital!

42
00:03:00,600 --> 00:03:01,933
- Hurry!
- Civilian hospital!

43
00:03:01,933 --> 00:03:04,500
- Move!
- Move!

44
00:03:04,500 --> 00:03:06,833
- What's going on?
- The battalion commander collapsed, sir.

45
00:03:06,833 --> 00:03:08,900
What? Why all of a sudden?

46
00:03:12,667 --> 00:03:15,267
I heard he ate the seaweed soup
made by the youngest cook

47
00:03:15,267 --> 00:03:17,633
and suddenly had trouble breathing.

48
00:03:17,633 --> 00:03:20,167
Under military law, is this assault
resulting in the death of a superior

49
00:03:20,167 --> 00:03:21,952
or distribution of harmful food?

50
00:03:21,952 --> 00:03:23,872
Jeez...

51
00:03:27,258 --> 00:03:28,512
Huh?

52
00:03:28,512 --> 00:03:30,724
[Military Mess Hall]
Jeez!

53
00:03:32,267 --> 00:03:34,367
His military life is totally
screwed now, huh?

54
00:03:37,733 --> 00:03:40,100
I have nothing to do with this seaweed soup!

55
00:03:40,100 --> 00:03:41,400
This is seriously unfair!

56
00:03:41,400 --> 00:03:43,233
Hey, Kang Sung Jae, say something!

57
00:03:43,233 --> 00:03:45,167
I think there's been a misunderstanding.

58
00:03:45,167 --> 00:03:46,667
This can't be happening...

59
00:03:46,667 --> 00:03:50,233
I heard it'd be insanely good
if I made it like this.

60
00:03:52,967 --> 00:03:57,333
I knew something like this would happen
because of his cooking, jeez.

61
00:03:58,656 --> 00:04:01,300
- Jeez...
- Oh my, oh my.

62
00:04:01,300 --> 00:04:03,067
What on earth is going on here?

63
00:04:03,067 --> 00:04:05,467
Did he actually put something in the food?

64
00:04:05,467 --> 00:04:08,900
I should've known when he said
this had to go in seaweed soup.

65
00:04:08,900 --> 00:04:11,367
So he did put something in it, huh?

66
00:04:11,367 --> 00:04:13,133
It wasn't anything special, though.

67
00:04:13,133 --> 00:04:15,967
Jeez, what in the world
did you put in there, you punk?

68
00:04:24,733 --> 00:04:26,100
Sir!

69
00:04:26,100 --> 00:04:27,300
Don't worry, sir!

70
00:04:27,300 --> 00:04:28,672
Like you said, we brought you

71
00:04:28,672 --> 00:04:30,433
to a nearby civilian hospital
instead of the medical unit.

72
00:04:30,433 --> 00:04:31,833
Are you okay, sir?

73
00:04:31,833 --> 00:04:34,833
I was so worried I thought
something serious had happened, sir!

74
00:04:38,733 --> 00:04:41,633
I've been to heaven.

75
00:04:41,633 --> 00:04:44,667
Please don't talk like that, sir!

76
00:04:44,667 --> 00:04:47,367
You're supposed to live a long life, sir.

77
00:04:48,233 --> 00:04:50,833
I met an angel

78
00:04:53,700 --> 00:04:57,667
and floated above the clouds,
you believe that?

79
00:05:01,700 --> 00:05:04,000
- Nurse!
- Someone is dying here!

80
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:05,033
Nurse!

81
00:05:05,033 --> 00:05:07,200
- Please hurry!
- Please hurry!

82
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:30,933
The perfect combination
of seaweed and sea urchin roe.

83
00:05:30,933 --> 00:05:33,633
Isn't this heaven right here?

84
00:05:33,633 --> 00:05:38,533
Of course, that was
before those punks appeared.

85
00:06:18,233 --> 00:06:20,533
What? This is actually amazing.

86
00:06:20,533 --> 00:06:24,100
Oh, really? Oh, that's a relief.

87
00:06:24,100 --> 00:06:25,700
Thank you, ma'am!

88
00:06:38,233 --> 00:06:39,433
What is this?

89
00:06:39,433 --> 00:06:41,633
Oh, it's perilla powder.

90
00:06:47,867 --> 00:06:52,733
It's asphyxiation caused by anaphylactic
shock from powdered perilla seeds.

91
00:06:58,433 --> 00:07:02,100
Sir!

92
00:07:02,100 --> 00:07:05,433
He just had trouble breathing for a moment
because of a perilla powder allergy

93
00:07:05,433 --> 00:07:06,967
and briefly passed out.

94
00:07:06,967 --> 00:07:09,567
I've given him some allergy medication,
so he just needs to take it.

95
00:07:13,767 --> 00:07:18,567
Didn't you know he can't eat pork bone soup
because of perilla powder?

96
00:07:19,933 --> 00:07:21,567
I'm sorry, sir.

97
00:07:21,567 --> 00:07:24,700
I should have taken extra care,
but I failed to be attentive enough.

98
00:07:24,700 --> 00:07:27,967
I'll make sure to properly retrain
the platoon leader and the cooks, sir.

99
00:07:27,967 --> 00:07:29,467
Seok Ho.

100
00:07:29,467 --> 00:07:30,500
Yes, sir!

101
00:07:30,500 --> 00:07:34,333
Don't be too hard on Ye Rin and the soldiers.

102
00:07:34,333 --> 00:07:37,067
If we let it slide, how do we know
this won't happen again?

103
00:07:37,067 --> 00:07:39,300
We need to discipline them
properly this time, sir.

104
00:07:45,267 --> 00:07:46,957
We're

105
00:07:46,957 --> 00:07:49,200
officers, aren't we?

106
00:07:51,700 --> 00:07:53,967
[Strict Vigilance, Perfect Mission Execution]
Can't you do it properly?

107
00:07:53,967 --> 00:07:56,100
Do you have any idea what you've done?

108
00:07:56,100 --> 00:07:58,900
You should treat cooking
like real combat out there!

109
00:07:58,900 --> 00:08:01,533
Deputy platoon leader, stop it.

110
00:08:01,533 --> 00:08:04,633
Punishing them won't make
the battalion commander better.

111
00:08:04,633 --> 00:08:08,367
Ma'am, if we let this slide,
the whole unit will fall apart.

112
00:08:08,367 --> 00:08:12,033
That sergeant went to rest alone
before mealtime was even over,

113
00:08:12,033 --> 00:08:14,500
and that private just cooked
with unauthorized ingredients.

114
00:08:14,500 --> 00:08:16,867
I understand what you're saying,

115
00:08:18,033 --> 00:08:22,733
but it's also my fault for letting him
make the seaweed soup.

116
00:08:22,733 --> 00:08:24,467
Pardon?

117
00:08:24,467 --> 00:08:26,733
So if you're going to blame someone,
blame me.

118
00:08:29,767 --> 00:08:31,333
Both of you, stand up!

119
00:08:31,333 --> 00:08:32,833
- Stand up!
- Stand up!

120
00:08:32,833 --> 00:08:35,067
Of all people, the battalion commander...

121
00:08:35,067 --> 00:08:37,567
- This is the Republic of Korea...
- Warrior.

122
00:08:37,567 --> 00:08:40,000
['The first dish is too difficult!' complete]
Quest successfully completed.

123
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:44,800
Level up! You can now use new recipes
and the affection-check skill.

124
00:08:44,800 --> 00:08:47,400
[Available Skills]

125
00:08:47,400 --> 00:08:49,967
[Affection Check]

126
00:08:53,200 --> 00:08:54,600
[Dislike 40%]

127
00:08:54,600 --> 00:08:58,233
The outpost's already a mess these days,
and you're just stirring things up more?

128
00:08:59,367 --> 00:09:03,333
[Dislike 60%]

129
00:09:03,333 --> 00:09:05,867
Hey, Kang Sung Jae!
What are you even looking at?

130
00:09:05,867 --> 00:09:08,200
Private Kang Sung Jae! It's nothing, sir!

131
00:09:09,900 --> 00:09:12,133
Sir! Yes, sir.

132
00:09:12,133 --> 00:09:14,333
Should I send these punks
straight to military court?

133
00:09:14,333 --> 00:09:15,333
Huh?

134
00:09:15,333 --> 00:09:17,000
Pardon?

135
00:09:20,900 --> 00:09:23,633
I'm deeply disappointed.

136
00:09:23,633 --> 00:09:27,400
How can you cooks
be so careless about ingredient selection?

137
00:09:27,400 --> 00:09:30,333
And above all,
the battalion commander's meal?

138
00:09:31,933 --> 00:09:34,433
[Dislike 50%]

139
00:09:34,433 --> 00:09:36,200
Private Kang Sung Jae.

140
00:09:36,200 --> 00:09:37,567
Private Kang Sung Jae!

141
00:09:37,567 --> 00:09:42,500
Is it true that you used sea urchin roe
and perilla powder in the seaweed soup?

142
00:09:42,500 --> 00:09:43,500
Yes, sir!

143
00:09:43,500 --> 00:09:45,200
- Sergeant Yoon Dong Hyun.
- Sergeant Yoon Dong Hyun!

144
00:09:45,200 --> 00:09:48,567
Are you authorized to cook
with non-supply ingredients?

145
00:09:48,567 --> 00:09:51,267
- No, sir.
- Exactly.

146
00:09:51,267 --> 00:09:52,967
That's what I'm saying.

147
00:09:52,967 --> 00:09:56,233
Where did that sea urchin roe even come from?

148
00:10:01,733 --> 00:10:04,367
I believe it's domestically sourced, sir!

149
00:10:11,200 --> 00:10:12,800
Did I...

150
00:10:13,667 --> 00:10:15,767
Am I asking for the origin right now?

151
00:10:17,000 --> 00:10:19,968
I think the Sergeant Major put it there, sir.

152
00:10:19,968 --> 00:10:21,088
[Menu]

153
00:10:23,867 --> 00:10:26,000
You can't just put anything in, sir!

154
00:10:26,000 --> 00:10:27,700
- Jeez, not again!
- Shh.

155
00:10:27,700 --> 00:10:29,733
What's that?

156
00:10:29,733 --> 00:10:32,133
If a sea urchin lays eggs, what is it?

157
00:10:32,133 --> 00:10:34,533
Sea urchin... eggs?

158
00:10:36,933 --> 00:10:40,900
The mess hall fridge isn't his
personal fridge. What did he do, seriously?

159
00:10:40,900 --> 00:10:42,000
Throw everything away.

160
00:10:42,000 --> 00:10:43,900
Yes, sir!

161
00:10:43,900 --> 00:10:49,733
Fortunately, the benevolent battalion
commander has decided to show leniency.

162
00:10:49,733 --> 00:10:51,367
But

163
00:10:52,000 --> 00:10:54,567
if something like this happens again,

164
00:10:54,567 --> 00:10:56,767
I, Hwang Seok Ho,

165
00:10:56,767 --> 00:10:58,600
will show no mercy.

166
00:11:00,233 --> 00:11:02,233
- Dismissed.
- Attention!

167
00:11:02,233 --> 00:11:04,600
- Salute.
- Hooah!

168
00:11:05,333 --> 00:11:07,200
- At ease.
- At ease!

169
00:11:30,900 --> 00:11:32,067
Communications security,

170
00:11:32,067 --> 00:11:33,800
this is Hwang Seok Ho.

171
00:11:34,600 --> 00:11:37,400
Can I review Private Kang Sung Jae's
service record again?

172
00:11:49,067 --> 00:11:51,100
Hey, Kang Sung Jae.

173
00:11:51,100 --> 00:11:52,300
Private Kang Sung Jae!

174
00:11:52,300 --> 00:11:55,033
Didn't I tell you to just stay put?

175
00:11:55,033 --> 00:11:56,033
I'm sorry, sir!

176
00:11:56,033 --> 00:11:58,433
Sea urchin roe and perilla powder?

177
00:11:58,433 --> 00:12:00,533
You, seriously...

178
00:12:01,200 --> 00:12:03,533
Do you think this is a joke?

179
00:12:06,067 --> 00:12:08,667
Communications security!
This is Sergeant Yoon Dong Hyun, mess hall.

180
00:12:08,667 --> 00:12:10,733
Sir! Private First Class Tak Mun Ik,
admin section.

181
00:12:10,733 --> 00:12:12,067
What's up?

182
00:12:12,067 --> 00:12:14,500
The company commander said
the new recruit will be on patrol duty.

183
00:12:14,500 --> 00:12:17,233
All of a sudden? Am I supposed to
clean this up alone?

184
00:12:17,233 --> 00:12:18,233
Sir!

185
00:12:18,233 --> 00:12:20,867
Sergeant Yoon Dong Hyun is asking
if he has to clean alone. What should I say?

186
00:12:20,867 --> 00:12:23,867
Of course he should clean it up alone!
Or should I help him?

187
00:12:23,867 --> 00:12:25,000
Hey, Yoon Dong Hyun!

188
00:12:25,000 --> 00:12:29,267
So who told you to leave your junior
and just lie around in the barracks?

189
00:12:29,267 --> 00:12:32,500
How many times did I tell you
to be careful with Kang Sung Jae?

190
00:12:35,800 --> 00:12:41,433
[Dislike 70%]

191
00:12:43,833 --> 00:12:45,200
Private Kang Sung Jae.

192
00:12:45,200 --> 00:12:47,133
Private Kang Sung Jae!

193
00:12:47,133 --> 00:12:50,267
Do you know why they call
this place the Stairway to Heaven?

194
00:12:50,267 --> 00:12:52,000
One wrong move,
and you'll actually end up there.

195
00:12:52,000 --> 00:12:53,333
So you should be careful.

196
00:12:53,333 --> 00:12:56,067
Alright, let's go to heaven!

197
00:12:56,067 --> 00:12:57,667
Yes, sir!

198
00:13:19,200 --> 00:13:21,133
- Private Kang Sung Jae.
- Private Kang Sung Jae!

199
00:13:21,133 --> 00:13:23,633
How is it after being assigned here?
Tough, isn't it?

200
00:13:23,633 --> 00:13:25,267
- No, sir!
- No?

201
00:13:25,267 --> 00:13:28,233
I already know everything.
You don't need to lie.

202
00:13:28,233 --> 00:13:31,400
I'm really fine. The senior soldiers
and platoon leader take good care of me, sir!

203
00:13:31,400 --> 00:13:33,600
No, there's no way you're fine.

204
00:13:33,600 --> 00:13:36,333
You lost your father
and enlisted just two months later.

205
00:13:36,333 --> 00:13:38,533
I know you're just pretending to be fine.

206
00:13:38,533 --> 00:13:41,600
No, sir. I just want to do well
in the military for my mother

207
00:13:41,600 --> 00:13:42,833
and younger sister at home.

208
00:13:42,833 --> 00:13:47,000
There's a saying, "what matters is
an unbreakable spirit,"

209
00:13:47,000 --> 00:13:50,533
but I cannot agree with that.

210
00:13:50,533 --> 00:13:53,233
If you force yourself to do your best,
you'll eventually break.

211
00:13:53,233 --> 00:13:57,133
I don't want you to push yourself
until you break, Private Kang Sung Jae.

212
00:14:07,667 --> 00:14:09,967
I've warned you several times.

213
00:14:09,967 --> 00:14:12,300
Don't leave your own food in the mess hall.

214
00:14:12,300 --> 00:14:15,400
Well, sea urchin roe
depends entirely on freshness...

215
00:14:15,400 --> 00:14:18,767
That sea urchin roe nearly got
the battalion commander into serious trouble.

216
00:14:18,767 --> 00:14:21,633
Jeez, let's call a spade a spade here, sir.

217
00:14:21,633 --> 00:14:25,267
Honestly, wasn't it actually
the perilla powder, not the sea urchin roe?

218
00:14:25,267 --> 00:14:28,433
And that was the new recruit
acting on his own.

219
00:14:28,433 --> 00:14:31,800
Jeez, exactly.

220
00:14:31,800 --> 00:14:32,960
[Personnel Record Card]
Even sending Kang Sung Jae

221
00:14:32,960 --> 00:14:34,467
to the kitchen in the first place...

222
00:14:34,467 --> 00:14:38,233
Frankly, I did warn you that sending
Kang Sung Jae to the mess hall was risky.

223
00:14:38,233 --> 00:14:41,500
You're the one who said "high risk,
high return" and sent him there, sir.

224
00:14:41,500 --> 00:14:42,900
I know. I know that very well.

225
00:14:42,900 --> 00:14:46,100
And because of that darn high risk,
we're all about to go down with him.

226
00:14:46,100 --> 00:14:49,033
The battalion commander
keeps saying it's fine,

227
00:14:49,033 --> 00:14:53,633
but from where I'm standing,
this could get all of us in serious trouble.

228
00:14:56,467 --> 00:14:59,300
We should transfer Private Kang Sung Jae.

229
00:15:00,500 --> 00:15:02,833
And where exactly
are you planning to send him now?

230
00:15:03,867 --> 00:15:05,633
TOD!

231
00:15:08,833 --> 00:15:12,533
Have you heard of TOD?

232
00:15:13,800 --> 00:15:16,767
- Not exactly, sir.
- Thermal Observation Device.

233
00:15:16,767 --> 00:15:17,933
It's a surveillance system used to monitor

234
00:15:17,933 --> 00:15:23,000
for possible North Korean submarines
or vessels in the dark sea at night.

235
00:15:24,333 --> 00:15:28,700
I believe it's an important position that
plays a key role in South Korea's security.

236
00:15:29,900 --> 00:15:32,300
What do you think?

237
00:15:32,300 --> 00:15:36,700
I believe there are no unnecessary posts
when it comes to national security, sir!

238
00:15:36,700 --> 00:15:40,100
That's right! No matter where you are,
you just have to do your duty.

239
00:15:40,100 --> 00:15:45,333
So what do you think about being reassigned
there instead of staying in the mess hall?

240
00:15:45,333 --> 00:15:46,367
To TOD, sir?

241
00:15:46,367 --> 00:15:47,933
There should be a spot at TOD,
shouldn't there?

242
00:15:47,933 --> 00:15:49,867
A spot can be made if needed,

243
00:15:49,867 --> 00:15:52,300
but sending him there doesn't
really change anything, does it?

244
00:15:52,300 --> 00:15:57,167
Sitting around doing surveillance must be
better than working in the mess hall, right?

245
00:15:58,464 --> 00:16:04,800
I'm not sure perilla powder in seaweed soup
is enough reason for a transfer.

246
00:16:04,800 --> 00:16:08,333
I can make the justification if I need to.

247
00:16:08,333 --> 00:16:11,200
I'm Company Commander Hwang Seok Ho.

248
00:16:17,933 --> 00:16:21,367
Last time, you said
I'd be suited for the mess hall.

249
00:16:23,100 --> 00:16:24,400
I did.

250
00:16:24,400 --> 00:16:26,400
But after observing you closely,

251
00:16:26,400 --> 00:16:30,033
I think you're too valuable
an asset to be stuck in the mess hall.

252
00:16:32,100 --> 00:16:34,700
Sir!

253
00:16:34,700 --> 00:16:37,333
Is this because of the seaweed soup?

254
00:16:37,333 --> 00:16:40,867
The battalion commander has already settled
everything. Do I need to go any further?

255
00:16:40,867 --> 00:16:42,767
It's just that I'm concerned.

256
00:16:42,767 --> 00:16:44,833
You're the first one up,
the last one to leave,

257
00:16:44,833 --> 00:16:46,100
and you don't even get weekends off.

258
00:16:46,100 --> 00:16:50,933
I think your current situation
is too harsh, Private Kang Sung Jae.

259
00:16:53,733 --> 00:16:54,733
I'm fine, sir!

260
00:16:54,733 --> 00:16:58,767
- It's fun learning things step by step.
- Alright.

261
00:17:00,833 --> 00:17:04,067
I understand exactly what you mean.

262
00:17:04,067 --> 00:17:06,367
Even though I'm treating you casually,

263
00:17:06,367 --> 00:17:08,700
it must not have been easy
to speak your mind honestly.

264
00:17:08,700 --> 00:17:10,400
Since

265
00:17:10,400 --> 00:17:12,867
I'm very charismatic.

266
00:17:15,067 --> 00:17:18,067
I've scheduled a counseling session
for you at the battalion tomorrow.

267
00:17:21,000 --> 00:17:26,667
Warrior, complete your
transfer quest within 72 hours.

268
00:17:26,667 --> 00:17:27,667
[Transfer Quest]

269
00:17:27,667 --> 00:17:28,667
[Use 'Chef's Eye' skill 3 times]

270
00:17:28,667 --> 00:17:29,900
[Three or more meal distributions]

271
00:17:29,900 --> 00:17:30,933
[Complete a 3-star dish using recipes]

272
00:17:30,933 --> 00:17:33,067
[Captain Hwang Seok Ho's Affection 50+]
Failure will result in

273
00:17:33,067 --> 00:17:37,033
losing the chance to become a legendary chef.

274
00:17:37,033 --> 00:17:39,100
A legendary chef?

275
00:17:39,100 --> 00:17:42,967
[Quest Remaining Time]

276
00:17:47,167 --> 00:17:48,300
Private Kang Sung Jae?

277
00:17:48,300 --> 00:17:49,300
Private Kang Sung Jae!

278
00:17:49,300 --> 00:17:52,500
It's just a counseling session,
so no need to be nervous.

279
00:17:52,500 --> 00:17:55,000
Every new recruit
goes through it at least once,

280
00:17:55,000 --> 00:17:56,667
so just go in and talk comfortably.

281
00:17:56,667 --> 00:17:58,533
Yes, sir!

282
00:18:00,640 --> 00:18:03,930
[Quest Remaining Time]

283
00:18:20,033 --> 00:18:23,800
I'm not even a soldier,
so just treat me casually, comfortably.

284
00:18:23,800 --> 00:18:25,633
Yes, understood!

285
00:18:32,533 --> 00:18:36,333
Your father passed away
right before your enlistment, didn't he?

286
00:18:36,333 --> 00:18:38,433
That must've been hard, right?

287
00:18:39,333 --> 00:18:42,567
I'm okay now. I've gotten better now.

288
00:18:42,567 --> 00:18:45,300
What kind of person
was your father, Sung Jae?

289
00:18:47,567 --> 00:18:49,133
My dad was...

290
00:18:49,133 --> 00:18:50,700
[Thank you to everyone who has loved
Sung Jae's Dining Table all this time]

291
00:18:50,700 --> 00:18:52,567
Here, please check.

292
00:18:59,290 --> 00:19:02,010
[Sung Jae's Dining Table]

293
00:19:07,500 --> 00:19:11,100
[Sung Jae's Dining Table]

294
00:19:15,467 --> 00:19:17,267
- Dad!
- Yeah?

295
00:19:17,267 --> 00:19:20,633
Why are you standing in the rain
like that, looking so gloomy?

296
00:19:22,667 --> 00:19:24,433
Son.

297
00:19:25,733 --> 00:19:28,933
I will never give up.

298
00:19:28,933 --> 00:19:32,833
I have you and your mom,
so I have to see this through to the end.

299
00:19:39,200 --> 00:19:43,200
My dad was the kind of man who never gave up.

300
00:19:44,000 --> 00:19:47,767
No matter what happened to him,
if it was for the sake of his family,

301
00:19:47,767 --> 00:19:50,633
he gritted his teeth and endured it.

302
00:19:51,700 --> 00:19:55,833
So Sung Jae, maybe you
take after him in responsibility too?

303
00:19:55,833 --> 00:19:57,533
I'm...

304
00:20:01,100 --> 00:20:03,100
How is military life treating you?

305
00:20:04,933 --> 00:20:10,133
The hardest part is things
I never expected suddenly happening.

306
00:20:10,133 --> 00:20:12,367
Like suddenly being
assigned to the mess hall.

307
00:20:12,367 --> 00:20:14,100
The mess hall?

308
00:20:14,100 --> 00:20:17,700
Do you think the mess hall
doesn't suit you, Sung Jae?

309
00:20:20,033 --> 00:20:26,567
[Military Mess Hall]

310
00:20:49,967 --> 00:20:51,200
Sir!

311
00:20:51,200 --> 00:20:52,500
I'm back from counseling!

312
00:20:52,500 --> 00:20:54,400
What did you say there?

313
00:20:54,400 --> 00:20:58,533
"Please help me escape from Kanglim!"
You said that, didn't you?

314
00:20:59,400 --> 00:21:03,067
No, sir! That's not it.

315
00:21:03,067 --> 00:21:05,800
Uh, Sergeant Yoon Dong Hyun?

316
00:21:05,800 --> 00:21:08,300
How did you end up in the mess hall anyway?

317
00:21:08,300 --> 00:21:11,333
What are you talking about?
I was ordered here by the company commander.

318
00:21:11,333 --> 00:21:16,300
And besides, I thought
it might be useful later in life.

319
00:21:17,467 --> 00:21:19,333
Private Kang Sung Jae!

320
00:21:20,033 --> 00:21:21,033
Sir!

321
00:21:21,033 --> 00:21:23,600
Did the counseling go well?

322
00:21:23,600 --> 00:21:25,600
Yes, sir. It went fine!

323
00:21:25,600 --> 00:21:30,167
Good, think carefully about what I said.

324
00:21:30,167 --> 00:21:32,100
Yes, sir!

325
00:21:32,100 --> 00:21:35,867
Sergeant Yoon Dong Hyun, we'd like to eat
some ramyeon with the team today.

326
00:21:35,867 --> 00:21:37,800
Then when do I get off duty?

327
00:21:37,800 --> 00:21:42,467
If you fulfill your duty as a cook
to the end, maybe you can get off duty.

328
00:21:43,300 --> 00:21:46,433
Do you think the mess hall
doesn't suit you, Sung Jae?

329
00:21:46,433 --> 00:21:50,233
I wish I could cook like my dad,

330
00:21:50,233 --> 00:21:53,167
but there's still so much I don't know,
and above all...

331
00:21:53,167 --> 00:21:59,000
[Dislike]

332
00:21:59,000 --> 00:22:03,167
I don't know what I'm supposed to do next.
It's just overwhelming.

333
00:22:03,167 --> 00:22:08,233
Don't think too far ahead. Just handle
what's in front of you, step by step.

334
00:22:08,900 --> 00:22:11,800
What's in front of me right now?

335
00:22:11,800 --> 00:22:16,067
If you don't give up,
you'll make it through somehow.

336
00:22:16,067 --> 00:22:18,300
Oh, you know how it is?

337
00:22:18,300 --> 00:22:21,000
Don't break the yolk!

338
00:22:23,667 --> 00:22:26,688
Can't he just eat cup ramyeon?

339
00:22:26,688 --> 00:22:27,967
Jeez.

340
00:22:27,967 --> 00:22:31,667
Sergeant Yoon Dong Hyun,
may I try cooking it myself?

341
00:22:33,900 --> 00:22:36,433
Just bring some ramyeon from the storage.

342
00:22:42,533 --> 00:22:45,367
And don't forget the right amount of water.

343
00:22:46,133 --> 00:22:48,600
The company commander
wants it cooked nice and chewy.

344
00:22:48,600 --> 00:22:50,700
Do you think you're guarding
the whole country below the 38th parallel?

345
00:22:50,700 --> 00:22:54,100
Still, Sergeant Yoon Dong Hyun,
you get to work under a roof, don't you?

346
00:22:54,100 --> 00:22:55,633
While we're out here

347
00:22:55,633 --> 00:22:57,800
in the summer heat
getting our faces peeled off.

348
00:22:57,800 --> 00:23:01,733
Hey, want to stand by the cauldron
and experience a steam bath?

349
00:23:03,833 --> 00:23:07,733
Jeez, what's the point of us
arguing about this?

350
00:23:07,733 --> 00:23:10,300
Sergeant Yoon Dong Hyun,
when's your next leave then?

351
00:23:10,300 --> 00:23:15,067
What are you talking about? I've got
a new recruit now, so I should take leave.

352
00:23:15,067 --> 00:23:17,733
Haven't you heard anything?

353
00:23:29,700 --> 00:23:30,700
Sergeant Yoon Dong Hyun!

354
00:23:30,700 --> 00:23:32,900
Don't talk to me right now.

355
00:23:35,167 --> 00:23:37,600
Are you seriously losing it? Let go.

356
00:23:37,600 --> 00:23:39,200
I think the eggs are spoiled, sir.

357
00:23:39,200 --> 00:23:41,400
They arrived yesterday.
How could they be spoiled?

358
00:23:41,400 --> 00:23:43,833
Stop talking nonsense.

359
00:23:46,733 --> 00:23:51,533
I'm busy enough already,
and now the eggs are acting up too?

360
00:23:57,800 --> 00:24:02,600
All the ones that came in yesterday
are spoiled, sir.

361
00:24:02,600 --> 00:24:07,300
This isn't a joke, you punk!
What can you even tell just by looking at it?

362
00:24:16,900 --> 00:24:22,784
I'm losing it. The company commander
won't eat ramyeon without eggs.

363
00:24:23,514 --> 00:24:25,464
Darn it.

364
00:24:32,267 --> 00:24:35,267
It's been seven days since the hen laid them.

365
00:24:35,267 --> 00:24:37,000
Found one!

366
00:24:37,000 --> 00:24:39,000
A fresh egg!

367
00:24:40,933 --> 00:24:42,733
Enjoy your meal, sir.

368
00:24:43,600 --> 00:24:45,200
- Yoon Dong Hyun.
- Sergeant Yoon Dong Hyun.

369
00:24:45,200 --> 00:24:47,100
What is going on?

370
00:24:47,100 --> 00:24:51,200
You even paid attention
to the ramyeon plating.

371
00:24:59,333 --> 00:25:01,800
Wow,

372
00:25:01,800 --> 00:25:03,767
the egg is perfectly cooked!

373
00:25:03,767 --> 00:25:06,833
Your skills are really improving
as you get closer to discharge.

374
00:25:06,833 --> 00:25:10,033
I just put in a bit of effort, sir.

375
00:25:10,033 --> 00:25:11,067
Alright, let's eat!

376
00:25:11,067 --> 00:25:12,800
Thank you for the meal, sir.

377
00:25:17,167 --> 00:25:21,200
[Dislike 20%]

378
00:25:29,167 --> 00:25:30,800
[Reduce Energy Use]

379
00:25:35,700 --> 00:25:36,933
Sergeant Yoon Dong Hyun.

380
00:25:36,933 --> 00:25:39,600
How did you end up in the mess hall anyway?

381
00:25:39,600 --> 00:25:43,400
Good, think carefully about what I said.

382
00:25:43,400 --> 00:25:44,967
- Huh?
- Sergeant Yoon Dong Hyun!

383
00:25:44,967 --> 00:25:47,567
May I try cooking it myself?

384
00:25:47,567 --> 00:25:49,900
Kang Sung Jae! Darn it.

385
00:25:52,600 --> 00:25:55,433
Make sure plastic goes with plastic,
cans with cans!

386
00:25:55,433 --> 00:25:58,100
Separate them properly
into correct bins! You know it, right?

387
00:25:58,100 --> 00:26:00,067
Yes, sir!

388
00:26:00,067 --> 00:26:03,567
Jeez, if only we could sort
people too. That'd be great.

389
00:26:03,567 --> 00:26:06,233
[Transfer Quest]

390
00:26:07,000 --> 00:26:08,933
[Use 'Chef's Eye' skill 3 times, 2/3]

391
00:26:08,933 --> 00:26:11,067
[Quest Remaining Time]
Not the rejects who can't even be recycled...

392
00:26:11,067 --> 00:26:12,367
Complete the quest!

393
00:26:12,367 --> 00:26:15,433
Gather all the competent ones together...

394
00:26:19,667 --> 00:26:21,267
Jeez, here he goes again!

395
00:26:21,267 --> 00:26:24,033
- I'm sorry, sir!
- Tell me, what exactly are you thinking?

396
00:26:24,033 --> 00:26:26,800
Still lost about who you are
and where you are?

397
00:26:26,800 --> 00:26:29,233
- No, sir!
- You're only good at talking back.

398
00:26:29,233 --> 00:26:31,367
Ugh, this is stressful.

399
00:26:34,233 --> 00:26:35,267
- Sir!
- Kang Sung Jae.

400
00:26:35,267 --> 00:26:37,400
Private Kang Sung Jae!

401
00:26:37,400 --> 00:26:39,433
What are you really?

402
00:26:39,433 --> 00:26:43,567
If you're going to act, do it properly.
Don't confuse people.

403
00:26:44,233 --> 00:26:45,733
What do you mean, sir?

404
00:26:45,733 --> 00:26:47,300
Still playing dumb?

405
00:26:47,300 --> 00:26:48,933
You...

406
00:26:50,067 --> 00:26:54,080
The company commander
ordered you to transfer to TOD, right?

407
00:26:54,080 --> 00:26:55,933
- Well...
- I mean Kang Sung Jae.

408
00:26:55,933 --> 00:26:59,400
The company commander is taking him to TOD.
Didn't you know that?

409
00:26:59,400 --> 00:27:02,033
You helped me because you felt bad
getting all the 'good stuff' alone?

410
00:27:02,033 --> 00:27:03,800
That's not it, sir!

411
00:27:03,800 --> 00:27:05,833
I'm not doing this because of leave.

412
00:27:05,833 --> 00:27:08,400
I'm just frustrated. Seriously frustrated.

413
00:27:08,400 --> 00:27:13,133
Do you really think it'll be easier
going to TOD instead of the mess hall?

414
00:27:13,133 --> 00:27:15,000
What are you talking about?

415
00:27:15,833 --> 00:27:17,433
Ma'am!

416
00:27:18,933 --> 00:27:20,600
Come in.

417
00:27:23,033 --> 00:27:24,667
Sir!

418
00:27:30,567 --> 00:27:32,400
Why didn't you tell me?

419
00:27:32,400 --> 00:27:33,700
What are you suddenly talking about?

420
00:27:33,700 --> 00:27:37,033
Did you tell Sung Jae to quit the mess hall?

421
00:27:37,033 --> 00:27:40,633
Hearing what the other guys say,
his condition isn't normal.

422
00:27:40,633 --> 00:27:42,800
They say he keeps gesturing at thin air.

423
00:27:42,800 --> 00:27:46,600
And at times,
he even flinches as if he sees a ghost.

424
00:27:46,600 --> 00:27:50,967
Even small things like this
seem like early warning signs.

425
00:27:50,967 --> 00:27:52,267
I am the platoon leader here.

426
00:27:52,267 --> 00:27:54,133
Yeah, everyone knows that.

427
00:27:54,133 --> 00:27:57,767
I make the decisions,
and I take responsibility for them.

428
00:27:57,767 --> 00:28:00,333
I just don't want to repeat
the same mistakes, and...

429
00:28:00,333 --> 00:28:02,016
A new recruit wouldn't even have the time

430
00:28:02,016 --> 00:28:04,733
to worry about
the battalion commander's allergies.

431
00:28:04,733 --> 00:28:07,733
Did I just say he can't handle it?

432
00:28:07,733 --> 00:28:11,233
I made the decision after I checked
all of Kang Sung Jae's counseling records.

433
00:28:11,233 --> 00:28:13,767
If you had checked it,
you'd understand more clearly.

434
00:28:13,767 --> 00:28:16,667
The counselor's evaluation result said...

435
00:28:16,667 --> 00:28:19,733
"Despite a difficult family background,

436
00:28:19,733 --> 00:28:22,167
he demonstrates strong motivation
for military service,

437
00:28:22,167 --> 00:28:24,933
and with sufficient adjustment time
after assignment,

438
00:28:24,933 --> 00:28:28,233
he appears capable of fulfilling
his military duties faithfully."

439
00:28:29,567 --> 00:28:33,900
Even with this, why are your commander
and the sergeant major so dissatisfied?

440
00:28:34,867 --> 00:28:37,000
Did you try the seaweed soup that day?

441
00:28:37,000 --> 00:28:40,000
Just as the battalion commander said,
it was excellent.

442
00:28:40,000 --> 00:28:43,767
Shouldn't you be more
worried about yourself first?

443
00:28:46,600 --> 00:28:49,067
Honestly, with your seniority,

444
00:28:49,067 --> 00:28:52,833
you're just doing a rookie lieutenant's job,
sitting there with a platoon leader armband.

445
00:28:53,800 --> 00:28:56,667
Even you yourself think
it's a bit strange, don't you?

446
00:28:57,333 --> 00:28:59,967
Why are you suddenly bringing that up?

447
00:28:59,967 --> 00:29:01,900
I mean,

448
00:29:03,200 --> 00:29:08,433
just take care of your own responsibilities.

449
00:29:14,133 --> 00:29:16,433
- Oh, Mom!
- Sung Jae!

450
00:29:16,433 --> 00:29:20,567
Everything okay? Are you eating properly?

451
00:29:22,240 --> 00:29:24,000
Don't worry about my meals.

452
00:29:24,000 --> 00:29:27,733
I'm a cook. No way I'd go hungry.

453
00:29:27,733 --> 00:29:29,200
Yeah, right.

454
00:29:29,200 --> 00:29:33,500
How is it that you resemble
your father so much, even in that?

455
00:29:35,633 --> 00:29:37,553
Mom,

456
00:29:37,553 --> 00:29:39,467
are you doing okay?

457
00:29:39,467 --> 00:29:42,000
Don't worry about me.

458
00:29:42,933 --> 00:29:44,544
How is it?

459
00:29:44,544 --> 00:29:47,000
Are people taking good care of you?

460
00:29:49,200 --> 00:29:51,296
Of course, they are.

461
00:29:52,800 --> 00:29:55,867
Everyone looks after me so well.

462
00:29:57,952 --> 00:30:00,267
That's really a relief.

463
00:30:00,267 --> 00:30:04,233
I'll learn cooking properly here
and go back home.

464
00:30:04,233 --> 00:30:07,967
Maybe it'll be useful
for something when I'm discharged.

465
00:30:07,967 --> 00:30:11,233
I am my father's son, after all.

466
00:30:17,767 --> 00:30:21,300
I thought my son is still a kid,

467
00:30:21,300 --> 00:30:23,533
but you're all grown up now.

468
00:30:24,467 --> 00:30:26,100
Don't get hurt anywhere, okay?

469
00:30:30,900 --> 00:30:34,767
I should get going now.
It's time for roll call.

470
00:30:34,767 --> 00:30:38,600
Well, I'll be on leave again soon anyway,

471
00:30:38,600 --> 00:30:40,733
so take care until then.

472
00:30:41,367 --> 00:30:43,033
Okay.

473
00:30:47,290 --> 00:30:51,962
[Korea Telecom]
(Watch on www,kisskh,la to support Admin)

474
00:30:53,667 --> 00:30:57,333
Would you like to acquire a new recipe?

475
00:30:58,767 --> 00:31:00,500
Yeah.

476
00:31:00,500 --> 00:31:02,600
Since it's come to this,

477
00:31:03,500 --> 00:31:06,233
I'll see how far I can take it.

478
00:31:11,467 --> 00:31:14,333
Recipe acquired.

479
00:31:18,967 --> 00:31:20,967
Kang Sung Jae, aren't you coming in?

480
00:31:20,967 --> 00:31:23,133
Yes, coming in, sir!

481
00:31:36,700 --> 00:31:38,533
What is this?

482
00:31:38,533 --> 00:31:41,760
Darn it, what is this?

483
00:31:42,458 --> 00:31:44,067
Jeez.

484
00:31:44,067 --> 00:31:46,633
Why does this rice smell like it's gone bad?

485
00:31:46,633 --> 00:31:48,433
- Hey!
- Sergeant Yoon Dong Hyun!

486
00:31:48,433 --> 00:31:49,833
Sergeant Major is looking for you.

487
00:31:49,833 --> 00:31:54,300
Whether it smells or not...

488
00:31:54,300 --> 00:31:56,067
Is that punk out his mind?

489
00:31:56,067 --> 00:31:57,467
Hey, Yoon Dong Hyun!

490
00:31:57,467 --> 00:32:00,733
The rice smells like rotten dog food now.
What are you going to do about it?

491
00:32:00,733 --> 00:32:03,833
Tell them to eat instant rice!

492
00:32:03,833 --> 00:32:05,867
What? Instant rice?

493
00:32:05,867 --> 00:32:07,800
What am I, some kind of alchemist?

494
00:32:07,800 --> 00:32:10,400
It smells because the rice is bad.
What else can I do?

495
00:32:10,400 --> 00:32:12,333
Has he lost it now?

496
00:32:12,333 --> 00:32:14,528
Just because you're about to leave
and I've been lenient,

497
00:32:14,528 --> 00:32:15,867
you think you can act freely?

498
00:32:15,867 --> 00:32:18,667
How am I supposed to leave
when I don't even have a successor?

499
00:32:18,667 --> 00:32:19,867
What did you say, you punk? You...

500
00:32:19,867 --> 00:32:21,700
What did you just say! You come here!

501
00:32:21,700 --> 00:32:23,033
You punk, come here!

502
00:32:23,033 --> 00:32:24,033
Come here!

503
00:32:24,033 --> 00:32:25,300
Come here, you punk!

504
00:32:25,300 --> 00:32:27,700
Come here!

505
00:32:42,967 --> 00:32:46,867
3-year-old rice, Grade D.

506
00:33:03,467 --> 00:33:07,533
Use vinegar to remove the smell of aged rice.

507
00:33:11,700 --> 00:33:14,933
[Spoiled rice smell removed successfully]
The smell has been removed using vinegar.

508
00:33:14,933 --> 00:33:18,833
[Level up]
Gained 50 EXP and leveled up.

509
00:33:22,800 --> 00:33:25,267
Rice, bean sprout soup.

510
00:33:25,267 --> 00:33:28,000
[Bean Sprout Soup]

511
00:33:29,067 --> 00:33:34,333
Warrior, the bean sprout soup's
salt level is currently too high.

512
00:33:34,333 --> 00:33:36,867
Pour in water to lower the salt level.

513
00:33:40,133 --> 00:33:42,267
[Salt level too high]

514
00:33:43,900 --> 00:33:49,233
[Bean Sprout Soup]

515
00:33:49,233 --> 00:33:51,800
Adding Cheongyang chili peppers will enhance

516
00:33:51,800 --> 00:33:54,733
[Cheongyang chili peppers for extra spice]
the spicy flavor and earn bonus points.

517
00:34:02,267 --> 00:34:05,433
[Bean Sprout Soup]

518
00:34:05,433 --> 00:34:09,067
[Spicy Bean Sprout Soup]

519
00:34:13,567 --> 00:34:15,400
Hey, hey!

520
00:34:15,400 --> 00:34:19,433
Who told you to mess
with the soup without permission?

521
00:34:19,433 --> 00:34:22,933
After what you did to the seaweed soup,
you still haven't learned your lesson?

522
00:34:22,933 --> 00:34:26,133
I just thought it was a bit too salty, sir.

523
00:34:26,133 --> 00:34:28,800
Whether it's salty or not,
why is that your concern?

524
00:34:28,800 --> 00:34:31,367
If you're leaving the mess hall anyway,
just leave quietly.

525
00:34:31,367 --> 00:34:33,267
Don't cause more trouble.

526
00:34:34,300 --> 00:34:36,900
Okay. It's hot.

527
00:34:41,767 --> 00:34:45,333
That guy's really high maintenance.

528
00:34:45,333 --> 00:34:47,867
Did he mess with the soup again or something?

529
00:34:52,433 --> 00:34:53,567
Enjoy your meal, sir.

530
00:34:53,567 --> 00:34:55,866
- Yeah.
- Enjoy your meal, sir.

531
00:34:55,866 --> 00:34:57,200
Jeez.

532
00:34:57,200 --> 00:34:59,600
Today's menu is boring again.

533
00:35:09,067 --> 00:35:11,467
Cereal for breakfast is fine
for a day or two,

534
00:35:11,467 --> 00:35:14,300
but I want a proper meal.

535
00:35:14,300 --> 00:35:16,100
Hey, Kim Kwan Cheol!

536
00:35:16,100 --> 00:35:19,833
- Enjoy your meal, sir.
- Who told you to eat cereal for breakfast?

537
00:35:19,833 --> 00:35:22,567
Don't you know skipping meals
can get you sent to discipline training?

538
00:35:22,567 --> 00:35:24,067
Would I be eating this if it were edible?

539
00:35:24,067 --> 00:35:29,433
You punk! It's not like
you'll die from eating this.

540
00:35:29,433 --> 00:35:32,133
You punk!

541
00:35:32,133 --> 00:35:34,100
You're so full of yourself.

542
00:35:36,100 --> 00:35:38,600
This is all paid by taxpayers!

543
00:35:38,600 --> 00:35:41,633
Just... eat it like this.

544
00:35:57,767 --> 00:36:00,000
Why does this taste refreshing?

545
00:36:00,000 --> 00:36:03,000
You're still hungover
from yesterday, aren't you, sir?

546
00:36:03,000 --> 00:36:08,467
This is really clearing me up,
perfect hangover cure!

547
00:36:08,467 --> 00:36:11,133
This is extraordinary!

548
00:36:21,434 --> 00:36:24,233
Wow.

549
00:36:24,233 --> 00:36:25,767
Hey, Yoon Dong Hyun!

550
00:36:25,767 --> 00:36:27,033
What's wrong, sir?

551
00:36:27,033 --> 00:36:29,400
See? It works.

552
00:36:29,400 --> 00:36:32,700
The stale smell is completely
gone from the rice.

553
00:36:34,467 --> 00:36:36,100
Wait...

554
00:36:42,033 --> 00:36:44,567
The refreshing taste of aspartic acid
meets Cheongyang chili peppers,

555
00:36:44,567 --> 00:36:45,867
creating a synergistic effect.

556
00:36:45,867 --> 00:36:48,833
It's more unexpected than coming across

557
00:36:48,833 --> 00:36:53,700
cool air conditioning in a shop
you randomly pass on a hot summer day.

558
00:37:01,367 --> 00:37:04,000
Jeez, did you get infected by parasites
or something? What's going on?

559
00:37:04,000 --> 00:37:06,467
The soup actually tastes pretty good today.

560
00:37:06,467 --> 00:37:09,200
Don't lie, you punk! If you're
going to trick someone, do it right.

561
00:37:09,200 --> 00:37:12,100
I hate it more than anything
when people mess with food.

562
00:37:12,100 --> 00:37:13,867
I'm serious, sir.

563
00:37:31,500 --> 00:37:32,533
Are you okay?

564
00:37:32,533 --> 00:37:36,033
Corporal Kim Kwan Cheol, I want to live!

565
00:37:37,933 --> 00:37:40,467
- Once this battle is over...
- Shut it!

566
00:37:40,467 --> 00:37:42,167
You want to die again or something?

567
00:37:42,167 --> 00:37:44,433
Stay sharp this time!

568
00:37:46,767 --> 00:37:50,467
See you on the other side.

569
00:37:50,467 --> 00:37:52,967
Charge! Forward!

570
00:38:33,233 --> 00:38:35,100
- Sergeant Major!
- Sergeant Major!

571
00:38:35,100 --> 00:38:39,100
Ah, it's refreshing!

572
00:38:57,700 --> 00:38:59,700
Let's go!

573
00:39:01,312 --> 00:39:03,018
Victory!

574
00:39:09,467 --> 00:39:15,767
This is the true victory of military rations!

575
00:39:18,667 --> 00:39:23,967
Bean sprout soup!

576
00:39:26,600 --> 00:39:29,300
Corporal Kim Kwan Cheol! Are you okay, sir?

577
00:39:29,300 --> 00:39:31,833
Yeah, I'm fine.

578
00:39:31,833 --> 00:39:35,033
What? What's going on with everyone?

579
00:39:45,200 --> 00:39:48,967
What is this? This refreshing taste
filling my mouth.

580
00:39:48,967 --> 00:39:52,900
It reminds me of that night
I came back from the club disappointed.

581
00:39:52,900 --> 00:39:56,233
Yeah! It's like the deep, clean taste

582
00:39:56,233 --> 00:40:00,576
of that 24-hour Jeonju bean sprout soup
I had back then.

583
00:40:00,576 --> 00:40:02,230
Wow.

584
00:40:09,178 --> 00:40:11,184
What?

585
00:40:17,600 --> 00:40:22,667
[Like 20%]

586
00:40:28,167 --> 00:40:30,000
[Use 'Chef's Eye' skill 3 times]

587
00:40:30,000 --> 00:40:31,700
[Three or more meal distributions]

588
00:40:31,700 --> 00:40:33,267
[Complete a 3-star dish using recipes]

589
00:40:33,267 --> 00:40:36,200
[Transfer Quest]
Quest not completed yet.

590
00:40:36,200 --> 00:40:40,933
Increase Captain Hwang Seok Ho's
affection to complete the transfer.

591
00:40:59,400 --> 00:41:00,633
What's going on?

592
00:41:00,633 --> 00:41:03,033
People would think
they haven't eaten in days.

593
00:41:03,033 --> 00:41:05,467
Seriously, this is...

594
00:41:09,633 --> 00:41:11,800
Sergeant Major!

595
00:41:11,800 --> 00:41:13,333
Are you okay, sir?

596
00:41:13,333 --> 00:41:15,167
Are you alright, sir?

597
00:41:17,100 --> 00:41:18,967
The broth is...

598
00:41:20,200 --> 00:41:22,000
It's nothing.

599
00:41:22,933 --> 00:41:24,267
Enjoy your meal.

600
00:41:24,267 --> 00:41:25,900
Eat up.

601
00:41:47,033 --> 00:41:50,700
After eating a hearty meal today
for the first time in ages, I feel alive!

602
00:41:50,700 --> 00:41:51,967
Honestly, I was surprised.

603
00:41:51,967 --> 00:41:54,967
It's been a while since I've felt such
a civilian vibe at the platoon mess.

604
00:41:54,967 --> 00:41:57,967
There's no way Yoon Dong Hyun
suddenly came to his senses,

605
00:41:57,967 --> 00:42:00,133
and he definitely wouldn't
have left it to Kang Sung Jae.

606
00:42:00,133 --> 00:42:03,200
Come on, that rookie
can't even take care of himself.

607
00:42:03,200 --> 00:42:06,467
Right? Did Yoon Dong Hyun
have some awakening?

608
00:42:07,867 --> 00:42:09,700
No way.

609
00:42:13,562 --> 00:42:14,650
[Rice]

610
00:42:17,400 --> 00:42:20,200
Sergeant Yoon Dong Hyun,
I'm seriously dying here, sir.

611
00:42:20,200 --> 00:42:22,333
After that seaweed soup incident
with the battalion commander,

612
00:42:22,333 --> 00:42:24,033
the company commander got super sensitive,

613
00:42:24,033 --> 00:42:26,567
and he made us empty the entire warehouse
for inventory check.

614
00:42:26,567 --> 00:42:28,333
And Sergeant Major,

615
00:42:28,333 --> 00:42:31,433
he acted like he didn't know anything
about the missing supplies.

616
00:42:33,033 --> 00:42:36,967
And now even the new supplies
are completely spoiled.

617
00:42:36,967 --> 00:42:40,600
People are already grumbling everywhere.

618
00:42:40,600 --> 00:42:42,867
Will talking about it make any difference?

619
00:42:42,867 --> 00:42:46,500
It seems worse since the suppliers
changed recently.

620
00:42:46,500 --> 00:42:48,600
I must be the fool for expecting
anything to be normal.

621
00:42:48,600 --> 00:42:51,700
Yeah. I'm the fool. Jeez.

622
00:42:51,700 --> 00:42:54,367
- Private Kang Sung Jae!
- Hey!

623
00:43:03,267 --> 00:43:05,167
Hey, hey!

624
00:43:05,167 --> 00:43:08,633
- Private Kang Sung Jae!
- Are you checking properly?

625
00:43:08,633 --> 00:43:11,367
If you slack off, you'll get wrecked later.

626
00:43:11,367 --> 00:43:14,633
Oxtail soup, June 17 next year,
total of 20 units received.

627
00:43:14,633 --> 00:43:17,567
Seasoned dried laver,
September 12, two boxes received.

628
00:43:17,567 --> 00:43:21,200
Army burger buns
must be used up by August 30.

629
00:43:21,200 --> 00:43:22,533
Okay, got it!

630
00:43:22,533 --> 00:43:24,333
Yes, sir!

631
00:43:31,033 --> 00:43:33,933
Sergeant Yoon Dong Hyun,
are you really just going to send him away?

632
00:43:33,933 --> 00:43:36,433
You need a junior soldier to cover,
so you can take leave.

633
00:43:36,433 --> 00:43:38,633
Of course I know that.

634
00:43:46,533 --> 00:43:47,800
Ma'am?

635
00:43:47,800 --> 00:43:49,467
Yeah.

636
00:43:49,467 --> 00:43:50,967
About Kang Sung Jae,

637
00:43:50,967 --> 00:43:54,100
can we keep him in the mess hall?

638
00:43:54,100 --> 00:43:55,400
Hey, Yoon Dong Hyun!

639
00:43:55,400 --> 00:43:58,633
You're about to start asking
for leave again, aren't you?

640
00:43:58,633 --> 00:44:01,500
I asked the company commander about it,

641
00:44:02,333 --> 00:44:04,367
but I'm not sure, either.

642
00:44:04,367 --> 00:44:09,000
Didn't you notice today's meal
was completely different from usual?

643
00:44:09,000 --> 00:44:13,267
You didn't even touch the spinach side dishes
or braised potatoes I made.

644
00:44:13,267 --> 00:44:17,300
But you cleaned out
every last drop of the bean sprout soup.

645
00:44:17,300 --> 00:44:18,700
What nonsense is that?

646
00:44:18,700 --> 00:44:20,700
So you didn't make the bean sprout soup?

647
00:44:20,700 --> 00:44:25,933
No, sir. Removing the stale smell
from the rice was also Kang Sung Jae's doing.

648
00:44:25,933 --> 00:44:27,533
What?

649
00:44:29,167 --> 00:44:31,367
Kang Sung Jae did that?

650
00:44:31,367 --> 00:44:33,000
Really?

651
00:44:36,700 --> 00:44:38,833
Sir!

652
00:44:40,500 --> 00:44:44,533
You've got time before dinner,
so rest while you can.

653
00:44:44,533 --> 00:44:50,000
Don't go putting on a show just because
you feel bad about leaving the mess hall.

654
00:44:50,000 --> 00:44:51,867
Yes, sir!

655
00:45:04,600 --> 00:45:06,300
But seriously,

656
00:45:06,300 --> 00:45:09,833
what did you do to the bean sprout soup?

657
00:45:10,733 --> 00:45:14,267
I just added a bit more water
and some chopped Cheongyang chili peppers.

658
00:45:14,267 --> 00:45:15,267
Really?

659
00:45:15,267 --> 00:45:17,167
Jeez, I thought it was something special.

660
00:45:17,167 --> 00:45:20,133
Well, I could do that much too.

661
00:45:20,900 --> 00:45:24,100
I think everyone liked it because
I just got the basic seasoning right.

662
00:45:24,100 --> 00:45:25,824
So what about me?

663
00:45:25,824 --> 00:45:28,067
I can't season food?

664
00:45:28,067 --> 00:45:32,067
Everyone has different tastes,
so it's not a big deal.

665
00:45:39,167 --> 00:45:41,100
You...

666
00:45:42,233 --> 00:45:45,200
Can't you just stay here?

667
00:46:00,933 --> 00:46:04,433
[Quest Remaining Time]
Complete the transfer quest.

668
00:46:12,867 --> 00:46:14,667
Sergeant Yoon Dong Hyun.

669
00:46:15,867 --> 00:46:17,152
I actually

670
00:46:18,016 --> 00:46:20,767
want to stay as a cook too.

671
00:46:25,167 --> 00:46:26,752
Well,

672
00:46:26,752 --> 00:46:28,933
the company commander won't listen anyway.

673
00:46:28,933 --> 00:46:31,633
What can you even do?

674
00:46:31,633 --> 00:46:34,667
Can't we change his mind?

675
00:46:34,667 --> 00:46:37,033
He's the type who decides and sticks to it.

676
00:46:37,033 --> 00:46:39,333
How are we supposed to
break through that stubbornness?

677
00:46:39,333 --> 00:46:42,733
If words don't work,
there must be another way.

678
00:46:42,733 --> 00:46:45,733
[Ki Young and Chikini]

679
00:46:45,733 --> 00:46:47,467
- Ugh!
- Ugh...

680
00:46:47,467 --> 00:46:49,367
Why are all the eggs spoiled, seriously!

681
00:46:49,367 --> 00:46:52,000
Wait, Sergeant Yoon Dong Hyun,
is there anything you're afraid of?

682
00:46:52,000 --> 00:46:55,000
Me? Do I look like I'm scared of anything?

683
00:46:55,000 --> 00:46:57,800
But they are so scary.
What are we supposed to do?

684
00:46:57,800 --> 00:46:59,267
What do you mean what do we do?

685
00:46:59,267 --> 00:47:01,733
Just go ask politely.

686
00:47:11,933 --> 00:47:13,690
Excuse me!

687
00:47:17,800 --> 00:47:19,296
Freeze!

688
00:47:29,433 --> 00:47:30,667
It's still piping hot.

689
00:47:30,667 --> 00:47:33,267
But I do think
we might be overreacting a bit.

690
00:47:33,267 --> 00:47:35,700
Will doing this really change anything?

691
00:47:35,700 --> 00:47:38,600
But we don't really have
any other option, do we?

692
00:47:38,600 --> 00:47:42,200
But why does it have to be pork cutlet,
of all dishes?

693
00:47:42,200 --> 00:47:45,533
Everyone likes pork cutlet, don't they?

694
00:47:45,533 --> 00:47:47,267
Yeah, true.

695
00:47:47,267 --> 00:47:49,567
There's no man in Korea
who doesn't like pork cutlet.

696
00:47:49,567 --> 00:47:51,933
They say truly delicious food
made with sincerity

697
00:47:51,933 --> 00:47:54,767
has the power to move people's hearts.

698
00:47:54,767 --> 00:47:57,100
Who even says that nonsense?

699
00:47:57,100 --> 00:47:58,467
That's complete nonsense.

700
00:47:58,467 --> 00:48:00,833
My father used to say that.

701
00:48:00,833 --> 00:48:06,133
No wonder it sounds like such a precious
and valuable piece of wisdom!

702
00:48:08,067 --> 00:48:10,767
[Pork Belly, Pork Shoulder]

703
00:48:10,767 --> 00:48:12,500
[Pork Belly]

704
00:48:12,500 --> 00:48:14,967
[Pork Shoulder]

705
00:48:15,633 --> 00:48:18,367
I think it's hard to make
pork cutlet with this.

706
00:48:18,367 --> 00:48:21,500
We need something like
pork loin or tenderloin.

707
00:48:21,500 --> 00:48:23,067
Can't we just make it anyway?

708
00:48:23,067 --> 00:48:25,067
It'll be tough to get that kind of cut,

709
00:48:25,067 --> 00:48:28,867
and we can't even go outside right now.

710
00:48:34,033 --> 00:48:37,733
Oh, right! She's coming!

711
00:48:52,533 --> 00:48:54,733
Smell!

712
00:48:57,100 --> 00:49:02,500
If soldiers don't eat properly,
how are they supposed to defend the country?

713
00:49:02,500 --> 00:49:04,267
Food motivation is the most important.

714
00:49:04,267 --> 00:49:05,867
Miss Jung!

715
00:49:08,967 --> 00:49:12,100
What's got you so eager to help
this old woman all of a sudden?

716
00:49:12,100 --> 00:49:15,633
Sergeant Yoon, who usually
acts so annoyed when called?

717
00:49:15,633 --> 00:49:17,933
Someone might misunderstand that.

718
00:49:17,933 --> 00:49:19,567
Well, Miss Jung.

719
00:49:19,567 --> 00:49:23,367
Could I ask you for a small favor?

720
00:49:26,000 --> 00:49:29,233
I knew it. So what is it?

721
00:49:35,167 --> 00:49:38,200
[Pork Loin]

722
00:49:42,333 --> 00:49:46,267
The muscle fibers are consistent,
and there's no excessive fat marbling.

723
00:49:46,267 --> 00:49:48,367
Wow, the meat is in excellent condition!

724
00:49:48,367 --> 00:49:52,067
I went through them and picked the best one.

725
00:49:52,067 --> 00:49:55,667
Cuts like this really
keep the juice locked in when fried.

726
00:49:55,667 --> 00:49:58,767
Seriously, how do you raise pigs
to get such quality meat?

727
00:49:58,767 --> 00:50:02,233
Well, with all the leftovers we have,
the pigs are always full.

728
00:50:02,233 --> 00:50:05,000
How could we not get good meat?

729
00:50:05,000 --> 00:50:06,633
By the way,

730
00:50:06,633 --> 00:50:08,733
discount available for
ROK Armed Forces personnel.

731
00:50:08,733 --> 00:50:09,900
Hooah!

732
00:50:09,900 --> 00:50:11,567
Ma'am!

733
00:50:13,333 --> 00:50:15,400
Have you ever fried pork cutlet before?

734
00:50:15,400 --> 00:50:19,300
This is my first time
frying anything in my life, sir!

735
00:50:19,300 --> 00:50:22,833
Then what gave you the confidence
to say you'd make pork cutlet?

736
00:50:24,666 --> 00:50:25,792
[Recipe unlocked]

737
00:50:29,567 --> 00:50:32,033
[Pork Cutlet]
Pork cutlet recipe unlocked!

738
00:50:57,600 --> 00:51:00,800
Wow, that color looks amazing. What is this?

739
00:51:00,800 --> 00:51:02,433
[Sung Jae's First Pork Cutlet]

740
00:51:03,867 --> 00:51:06,267
[Too Salty, Way Too Salty]

741
00:51:06,267 --> 00:51:09,267
It seems something went wrong.

742
00:51:10,467 --> 00:51:12,800
Yum! Oh, it's salty.

743
00:51:12,800 --> 00:51:14,967
Why is this so salty?

744
00:51:17,800 --> 00:51:20,700
[Season the prepared meat
with fine salt and pepper]

745
00:51:22,600 --> 00:51:24,800
I should have used fine salt for seasoning,

746
00:51:24,800 --> 00:51:27,733
but I think I used coarse salt by mistake.

747
00:51:27,733 --> 00:51:29,567
You did that on purpose, didn't you?

748
00:51:36,800 --> 00:51:39,400
[Frying temperature: optimal]

749
00:51:40,133 --> 00:51:42,500
Frying temperature is optimal.

750
00:52:14,733 --> 00:52:18,300
[Properly fried pork cutlet,
golden and crispy]

751
00:52:18,300 --> 00:52:20,000
How is it, Sergeant Yoon Dong Hyun?

752
00:52:20,000 --> 00:52:24,800
Not even the company commander
could resist this taste.

753
00:52:36,570 --> 00:52:39,233
Okay.

754
00:52:39,233 --> 00:52:44,400
I'll protect the country,

755
00:52:44,400 --> 00:52:48,033
and you just sleep

756
00:52:48,033 --> 00:52:51,600
and stretch your legs.

757
00:52:51,600 --> 00:52:54,367
That line is really something.

758
00:52:55,067 --> 00:52:56,700
[Company Commander's Office]
Come in!

759
00:52:58,800 --> 00:52:59,833
Sir!

760
00:52:59,833 --> 00:53:03,167
Oh, actually, I was about
to go to the mess hall

761
00:53:03,167 --> 00:53:05,067
to handle your reassignment.

762
00:53:05,067 --> 00:53:06,067
What's going on?

763
00:53:06,067 --> 00:53:10,167
I prepared a special meal
in case you are hungry, sir.

764
00:53:11,633 --> 00:53:15,333
All of a sudden? To me? Why?

765
00:53:15,333 --> 00:53:17,467
Well, that's...

766
00:53:17,467 --> 00:53:22,067
Do you think a simple pork cutlet
will change my mind?

767
00:53:22,067 --> 00:53:24,000
If it's alright with you,

768
00:53:24,000 --> 00:53:27,267
I'd like to remain a cook, sir.

769
00:53:29,367 --> 00:53:31,100
Private Kang Sung Jae.

770
00:53:33,000 --> 00:53:37,300
I honestly can't understand
what you're thinking.

771
00:53:37,300 --> 00:53:40,800
If you taste this, you'll understand
why I need to stay in the kitchen...

772
00:53:40,800 --> 00:53:42,433
What should I do?

773
00:53:43,133 --> 00:53:46,500
I don't really like pork cutlet.

774
00:54:01,900 --> 00:54:06,067
- What?
- He said he doesn't really like pork cutlet.

775
00:54:06,067 --> 00:54:07,744
He doesn't like pork cutlet?

776
00:54:07,744 --> 00:54:12,700
Why... why on earth?

777
00:54:13,400 --> 00:54:14,600
Ma'am!

778
00:54:14,600 --> 00:54:16,267
Yeah.

779
00:54:16,267 --> 00:54:17,767
Sung Jae, step outside for a moment.

780
00:54:17,767 --> 00:54:19,400
Yes, ma'am!

781
00:54:26,733 --> 00:54:29,467
I heard you fried some pork cutlet
and went to see the company commander?

782
00:54:29,467 --> 00:54:30,586
Yes.

783
00:54:31,633 --> 00:54:33,200
Good work.

784
00:54:33,200 --> 00:54:37,867
Whatever your position is, what matters
is finishing military service properly.

785
00:54:42,600 --> 00:54:45,633
I think I understand now.

786
00:54:45,633 --> 00:54:47,267
Huh?

787
00:54:48,133 --> 00:54:50,112
Why

788
00:54:50,112 --> 00:54:52,700
I worked so hard today.

789
00:54:55,767 --> 00:54:59,833
While making the pork cutlet,
that thought kept coming to me.

790
00:55:01,562 --> 00:55:03,267
So,

791
00:55:03,267 --> 00:55:06,600
this is why food made with sincerity

792
00:55:06,600 --> 00:55:10,133
can't help but move people's hearts.

793
00:55:11,033 --> 00:55:17,133
But honestly, it makes me sad that
it's just getting cold without even a chance

794
00:55:17,900 --> 00:55:20,067
to let the company commander try it.

795
00:55:23,100 --> 00:55:25,567
Send him to TOD tomorrow.

796
00:55:27,400 --> 00:55:29,400
May I ask just one thing, sir?

797
00:55:29,400 --> 00:55:30,400
What is it?

798
00:55:30,400 --> 00:55:35,133
Do you believe your own judgment
is more important than a soldier's will?

799
00:55:35,133 --> 00:55:37,033
Jeez, Ye Rin.

800
00:55:37,033 --> 00:55:38,767
Actually, I want to ask you something.

801
00:55:38,767 --> 00:55:42,167
What on earth do you see in that kid
that makes you keep him in the kitchen?

802
00:55:42,167 --> 00:55:45,667
Since Sung Jae came, meal satisfaction
among soldiers has improved a lot.

803
00:55:45,667 --> 00:55:48,200
That's just because Yoon Dong Hyun
is terrible at cooking.

804
00:55:48,200 --> 00:55:52,733
I saw Private Kang Sung Jae
fix the strong odor from the stale rice.

805
00:55:52,733 --> 00:55:55,200
Have you tried the bean sprout soup he made?

806
00:55:55,200 --> 00:55:57,467
The soldiers finished every last drop.

807
00:55:57,467 --> 00:56:00,300
This is the factor
to objectively evaluate a soldier, sir.

808
00:56:00,300 --> 00:56:01,700
Not just a few documents.

809
00:56:01,700 --> 00:56:05,267
You keep trying to lecture me
just because I'm speaking nicely.

810
00:56:05,267 --> 00:56:07,867
Cho Ye Rin.

811
00:56:08,867 --> 00:56:12,933
Have you already forgotten
why you came back to Kanglim?

812
00:56:16,600 --> 00:56:20,400
It probably won't change anything,
but can I try it?

813
00:56:22,167 --> 00:56:24,167
Yes, of course, ma'am.

814
00:56:26,426 --> 00:56:28,250
[Military Mess Hall]

815
00:56:33,300 --> 00:56:36,900
I'm glad I could serve it to you, ma'am!

816
00:56:36,900 --> 00:56:38,600
I'll enjoy it.

817
00:56:43,333 --> 00:56:47,433
You know, it's not something I can decide.

818
00:56:48,433 --> 00:56:49,567
No, it's all right.

819
00:56:49,567 --> 00:56:52,100
If you enjoy it,

820
00:56:52,100 --> 00:56:55,133
then I feel like I've done my part.

821
00:56:59,167 --> 00:57:01,967
[Quest Remaining Time]

822
00:57:01,967 --> 00:57:04,000
[Ending Chef's Path]

823
00:57:04,000 --> 00:57:07,000
Transfer quest failed.

824
00:57:07,000 --> 00:57:09,967
Ending the path of a chef.

825
00:57:15,067 --> 00:57:20,300
Even with all my sincerity in cooking,
I still couldn't change anything.

826
00:57:22,367 --> 00:57:24,500
And so,

827
00:57:24,500 --> 00:57:29,367
the life I kept running away from
never changed, either.

828
00:58:42,967 --> 00:58:44,333
Emergency!

829
00:58:44,333 --> 00:58:46,833
- Emergency!
- They're asking to be sent back north.

830
00:58:46,833 --> 00:58:49,333
If we go back, we're all really going to die.

831
00:58:49,333 --> 00:58:52,133
And now you're showing off
food someone else made?

832
00:58:52,133 --> 00:58:53,633
Why don't you try making it yourself?

833
00:58:53,633 --> 00:58:55,433
Suddenly, from National Assembly members
to Division Commander...

834
00:58:55,433 --> 00:58:56,833
Now is not the time for that.

835
00:58:56,833 --> 00:58:58,233
Is it braised pollock fillet?

836
00:58:58,233 --> 00:59:00,500
Are you saying
there's a problem with the meal?

837
00:59:00,500 --> 00:59:01,833
Private Kang Sung Jae! I'm sorry, sir!

838
00:59:01,833 --> 00:59:04,064
[Frozen pollock]
Why do you think this is always voted

839
00:59:04,064 --> 00:59:05,833
the worst food by active-duty soldiers?

840
00:59:05,833 --> 00:59:09,033
It seems we couldn't get rid of
the fishy smell of frozen food.

841
00:59:09,033 --> 00:59:11,433
Then fix it no matter what!

842
00:59:11,433 --> 00:59:12,433
We don't have time.

843
00:59:12,433 --> 00:59:14,667
- Warning!
- It looks like there was an incident.

844
00:59:14,667 --> 00:59:16,400
What on earth did you do?
